Bootstrap: docker
From: condaforge/miniforge3:24.3.0-0

%labels
    Maintainer sdweave2@ncsu.edu
    Source https://github.com/AnantharamanLab/VIBRANT
    Version 1.2.1

%help
    VIBRANT (Virus Identification By iteRative ANnoTation) — automated
    recovery, annotation, and curation of microbial viruses, and
    evaluation of viral community function from genomic sequences
    (metagenomes, genomes, metagenome-assembled genomes). Uses a hybrid
    machine learning / protein similarity approach on prodigal-predicted
    genes to identify viruses.

    Usage:
        apptainer run VIBRANT.sif -i <input.fasta> [options]

    Options:
        -i         Input fasta file of sequences to classify (required)
        -f         Format of input: nucl or prot (default nucl)
        -t         Number of parallel processors to use
        -folder    Output folder directory
        -no_plot   Suppress figure/plot generation
        -h         Show help menu and exit

    Databases:
        VIBRANT requires ~11GB of reference databases (KEGG, Pfam, VOG)
        that are NOT bundled in this image. Download and compile them
        with VIBRANT_setup.py into a persistent directory (bind-mount one
        under /rs1 or /share) before running real jobs.

    Example:
        apptainer run VIBRANT.sif -i contigs.fasta -t 4

%post -c /bin/bash
    set -e
    export DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

    # Hazel bind-mount points
    mkdir -p /rs1 /share /home /usr/local/usrapps

    # AUTHORITATIVE: bioconda package "vibrant" version 1.2.1. mamba (not
    # classic conda) resolves this combined conda-forge+bioconda request
    # in minutes instead of hanging indefinitely (CLAUDE.md lesson 2).
    mamba create -n vibrant -y -c conda-forge -c bioconda "vibrant=1.2.1"
    mamba clean -afy

%environment
    export DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
    export PATH="/opt/conda/envs/vibrant/bin:$PATH"

%runscript
    exec VIBRANT_run.py "$@"

%test
    set -e
    VIBRANT_run.py -h
